Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. In small mixing bowl, combine nuts, sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over bottom of pastry shell. In large bowl, combine pumpkin, EAGLE BRAND(R), eggs, remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, and ginger; mix well. Pour filling over nut mixture in pie shell. Bake for 15 minutes. Reduce oven to 350 degrees F; continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean. Cool. Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.